    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Saying only \"diabetes\" or \"açúcar baixo\" without standard structure.  \n  ✔ Use diabetic emergency on board plus conscious/unconscious status.\n\n- ❌ Delaying diversion while waiting to see if sugar \"works.\"  \n  ✔ If unconscious or seizing, divert and request medical assistance.\n\n- ❌ Giving insulin dosing details on frequency.  \n  ✔ Report condition and assistance required — keep it operational.\n\n- ❌ Cancelling ambulances after partial improvement.  \n  ✔ Keep medical assistance for landing after a serious diabetic event.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Diabetic Emergency On Board, Passenger Unconscious, Request Medical Assistance\n\n**Pronunciation:** dy-uh-BET-ik ih-MER-jen-see on BORD, PASS-en-jer un-KON-shus, reh-KWEST MED-ih-kul uh-SIS-tuns\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Diabetic → dy-uh-BET-ik\n- Emergency → ih-MER-jen-see\n- Unconscious → un-KON-shus\n- Seizure → SEE-zher\n\nPractice:\n\nDiabetic emergency... passenger unconscious... request medical assistance.\n\nTogether:\n\nPan Pan Pan Pan Pan Pan, Approach, diabetic emergency on board, passenger unconscious, request priority landing.",
