    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Explaining symptoms at length before donning oxygen.  \n  ✔ Oxygen and descent first — then communicate.\n\n- ❌ Using only \"falta de ar\" without standard terms.  \n  ✔ Use hypoxia / symptoms of hypoxia / rapid decompression as applicable.\n\n- ❌ Leveling high because \"we feel better for a moment.\"  \n  ✔ Descend to a safe altitude and reassess on oxygen.\n\n- ❌ Forgetting medical assistance after occupant hypoxia.  \n  ✔ Request medical assistance if anyone remains impaired.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Hypoxia, Crew on Oxygen, Descending to Ten Thousand\n\n**Pronunciation:** hy-POK-see-uh, KROO on OK-sih-jen, dih-SEND-ing too TEN THOW-zund\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Hypoxia → hy-POK-see-uh\n- Oxygen → OK-sih-jen\n- Descending → dih-SEND-ing\n- Decompression → dee-kum-PRESH-un\n\nPractice:\n\nHypoxia... crew on oxygen... emergency descent.\n\nTogether:\n\nMayday Mayday Mayday, Control, hypoxia, crew on oxygen, descending to ten thousand feet.",
