    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Calling every cabin crew member \"purser.\"  \n  ✔ Purser is the senior cabin leader; others are flight attendants.\n\n- ❌ Using only \"chefe de cabine\" in an English exam answer.  \n  ✔ Prefer flight purser.\n\n- ❌ Confusing purser with first officer.  \n  ✔ Purser is cabin; first officer is flight deck.\n\n- ❌ Briefing random attendants and bypassing the purser on a multi-attendant crew.  \n  ✔ Brief the purser; let cabin leadership cascade the plan.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Flight Purser Reports Cabin Secure\n\n**Pronunciation:** FLYT PUR-ser rih-PORTS KAB-in suh-KYOOR\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Purser → PUR-ser\n- Senior → SEEN-yer\n- Cabin → KAB-in\n- Secure → suh-KYOOR\n\nPractice:\n\nFlight purser... senior cabin crew... cabin secure.\n\nTogether:\n\nFlight purser reports cabin secure, ready for landing.",
