    "icaoSpeakText": "Cabin crew are the crew members responsible for passenger safety and cabin emergency procedures. In an emergency they secure the cabin, manage passengers, report conditions to the flight deck, and carry out commands such as brace or evacuate. The pilots then communicate with ATC using that cabin information.",
    "missionBrief": "Today's lesson covers Cabin Crew — the collective term for crew members who work in the passenger cabin, including flight attendants and the flight purser, responsible for cabin safety, passenger care, and emergency procedures.\n\nICAO English uses cabin crew as the group name. Pilots must know when to say cabin crew versus flight attendant versus flight purser.\n\nFor H130 ICAO Delta academy operations in Brazil, many flights operate without dedicated cabin crew. The vocabulary remains essential for Part 1 comprehension, airline scenarios, and clear answers about who manages passengers in an emergency.\n\nMaster: cabin crew, cabin secure, cabin report, passenger safety.",
    "captainTeaching": "Cabin crew is the umbrella term.\n\nUnder it: flight attendants and, when assigned, a flight purser.\n\nBrazilian Portuguese: tripulação de cabine. Use cabin crew in ICAO English.\n\nDo not say \"the stewards\" in a formal exam answer. Do not call pilots cabin crew.\n\nIn H130 Brazilian operations, passenger safety may sit entirely with the pilot. Still answer role questions with standard airline vocabulary when the scenario is multi-crew.\n\nWhen cabin crew speak, listen for safety content: secure, smoke, medical, exits. That content becomes your ATC message if the ground needs to act.",
    "operationalContext": "On a multi-crew airliner scenario into Guarulhos, cabin crew complete the secure check and report ready for landing.\n\nLater, cabin crew report a passenger allergic reaction. Pilots declare Pan Pan and request medical assistance.\n\nOn an H130 charter with no cabin crew, the pilot briefs passengers directly. For the exam question \"Who is responsible for passenger cabin safety on an airliner?\" the answer remains cabin crew.",
    "sayItCoach": "Cabin crew report cabin secure, ready for approach.",
    "icaoModelAnswer": "Cabin crew are the crew members responsible for passenger safety and cabin emergency procedures. In an emergency they secure the cabin, manage passengers, report conditions to the flight deck, and carry out commands such as brace or evacuate. The pilots then communicate with ATC using that cabin information.",
