    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Using only \"comandante\" in an English exam answer.  \n  ✔ Prefer captain or pilot-in-command.\n\n- ❌ Delaying a safety decision to avoid \"bothering\" ATC.  \n  ✔ Decide, then communicate intentions promptly.\n\n- ❌ Saying personal authority phrases instead of operational intentions.  \n  ✔ Transmit diverting / unable / emergency — not speeches about rank.\n\n- ❌ Confusing pilot flying with pilot-in-command.  \n  ✔ The first officer may fly; the captain may still be PIC.",
