    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Calling any extra pilot on board a relief pilot without duty qualification.  \n  ✔ Relief pilot means qualified to take the duty seat under procedure.\n\n- ❌ Confusing relief pilot with check pilot.  \n  ✔ Relief covers fatigue/duty; check covers evaluation.\n\n- ❌ Transferring control silently during a critical phase.  \n  ✔ Use clear verbal transfer and avoid sterile-cockpit conflicts.\n\n- ❌ Assuming the relief pilot automatically becomes PIC.  \n  ✔ PIC authority follows formal designation and SOP.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Relief Pilot Taking Duty Seat\n\n**Pronunciation:** rih-LEEF PY-lut TAY-king DOO-tee SEET\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Relief → rih-LEEF\n- Pilot → PY-lut\n- Fatigue → fuh-TEEG\n- Transfer → TRANS-fer\n\nPractice:\n\nRelief pilot... transfer of control... fatigue management.\n\nTogether:\n\nRelief pilot taking the seat, control transferred, clearance unchanged.",
