    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Calling every instructor a relief pilot.  \n  ✔ Use check pilot / instructor for assessment roles.\n\n- ❌ Announcing check-ride details unnecessarily on frequency.  \n  ✔ Use standard operational ATC English unless relevant.\n\n- ❌ Freezing CRM because \"the examiner is watching.\"  \n  ✔ Make safety callouts anyway — that is the standard.\n\n- ❌ Unclear \"I have control\" discipline during intervention.  \n  ✔ Use clear transfer-of-control words immediately.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Check Pilot, Proficiency Check, I Have Control\n\n**Pronunciation:** CHEK PY-lut, pruh-FISH-en-see CHEK, EYE hav kun-TROHL\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Check → CHEK\n- Proficiency → pruh-FISH-en-see\n- Intervention → in-ter-VEN-shun\n- Control → kun-TROHL\n\nPractice:\n\nCheck pilot... proficiency check... I have control.\n\nTogether:\n\nCheck pilot intervening, I have control, going around.",
