    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Staying in freezing rain to complete the approach.  \n  ✔ Exit immediately — divert if necessary.\n\n- ❌ Saying only \"gelo\" without freezing rain.  \n  ✔ Name freezing rain so ATC understands the mechanism.\n\n- ❌ Accepting a hold in known freezing precipitation.  \n  ✔ Unable hold — request vectors clear of freezing rain.\n\n- ❌ Soft language when ice is rapid.  \n  ✔ Use immediate and, if needed, Pan Pan or Mayday.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Freezing Rain, Request Immediate Diversion\n\n**Pronunciation:** FREE-zing RAYN, reh-KWEST ih-MEE-dee-ut di-VER-zhun\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Freezing → FREE-zing\n- Rain → RAYN\n- Immediate → ih-MEE-dee-ut\n- Diversion → di-VER-zhun\n\nPractice:\n\nFreezing rain... request immediate diversion...\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, freezing rain, severe icing, request immediate diversion.",
