    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Calling it only \"garoa\" on an ICAO frequency.  \n  ✔ Use freezing drizzle.\n\n- ❌ Staying in the layer because accretion seems slow.  \n  ✔ Exit — slow ice still becomes dangerous.\n\n- ❌ Not stating icing intensity with the precipitation type.  \n  ✔ Report freezing drizzle and light/moderate/severe icing.\n\n- ❌ Accepting holds in freezing drizzle.  \n  ✔ Request vectors clear of freezing precipitation.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Freezing Drizzle at Five Thousand\n\n**Pronunciation:** FREE-zing DRIZ-ul at five THOW-zend\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Freezing → FREE-zing\n- Drizzle → DRIZ-ul\n- Thousand → THOW-zend\n- Icing → EYE-sing\n\nPractice:\n\nFreezing drizzle... light icing...\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, freezing drizzle at five thousand, request descent.",
