    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Waiting for obvious white rime before reporting icing.  \n  ✔ Clear ice may be transparent — report performance loss and icing early.\n\n- ❌ Reporting \"gelo\" without intensity or altitude.  \n  ✔ Include moderate/severe and altitude.\n\n- ❌ Holding in continuous clear-ice accretion.  \n  ✔ Request vectors clear of icing.\n\n- ❌ Confusing clear ice with frost on a parked aircraft only.  \n  ✔ Clear ice is an in-flight accretion hazard in supercooled droplets.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Clear Ice, Moderate Icing, Request Descent\n\n**Pronunciation:** KLEER EYES, MOD-er-it EYE-sing, reh-KWEST deh-SENT\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Clear → KLEER\n- Ice → EYES\n- Moderate → MOD-er-it\n- Icing → EYE-sing\n\nPractice:\n\nClear ice... moderate icing... request descent...\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, clear ice at four thousand, moderate icing, request descent.",
