    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Fighting the downdraft toward rising terrain.  \n  ✔ Turn toward lower terrain / request climb; do not sink into the ridge.\n\n- ❌ Reporting only \"turbulence\" when wave is the cause.  \n  ✔ Say mountain wave — it explains altitude loss and helps forecasts.\n\n- ❌ Flying under lenticulars for a \"smooth ride.\"  \n  ✔ Rotors often hide beneath; avoid the lee rotor zone.\n\n- ❌ Delayed PIREP after recovering.  \n  ✔ Report while the information is still useful to ATC and traffic.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** ANAC123, Moderate Mountain Wave, Request Climb\n\n**Pronunciation:** AY-nak WUN TOO THREE, MOD-er-it MOUN-tin WAYV, reh-KWEST KLYME\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Mountain → MOUN-tin\n- Wave → WAYV\n- Moderate → MOD-er-it\n- Downdraft → DOWN-draft\n\nPractice:\n\nModerate mountain wave... altitude loss... request climb.\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, moderate mountain wave, altitude loss one thousand feet, request climb.",
