    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Returning immediately without checking landing weight vs MLW.  \n  ✔ Calculate landing weight; hold or divert if above MLW.\n\n- ❌ Not telling ATC why you need to hold after a return.  \n  ✔ State: hold to reduce landing weight / above MLW.\n\n- ❌ Using only structural MLW on a short wet runway.  \n  ✔ Apply performance-limited landing weight when more restrictive.\n\n- ❌ Treating overweight landing as routine.  \n  ✔ Overweight landing is exceptional; plan to avoid it.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** ANAC123, Request Hold to Reduce Landing Weight\n\n**Pronunciation:** AY-nak WUN TOO THREE, reh-KWEST HOLD too ri-DOOS LAN-ding WAIT\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Request → reh-KWEST\n- Hold → HOLD\n- Reduce → ri-DOOS\n- Landing → LAN-ding\n- Weight → WAIT\n\nPractice:\n\nRequest hold... reduce landing weight... above maximum landing weight.\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, request hold to reduce landing weight, currently above maximum landing weight.",
