    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Using Vref terminology on H130 approaches.  \n  ✔ Use AFM approach speed / on profile language.\n\n- ❌ Defining Vref as any approach speed without the 1.3 VS basis.  \n  ✔ State the regulatory/performance definition with landing configuration.\n\n- ❌ Ignoring wind additives in exam answers about approach speed.  \n  ✔ Mention headwind and gust additives per typical SOP concepts.\n\n- ❌ Accepting ATC speed control that destabilizes the helicopter approach.  \n  ✔ State unable and request spacing when necessary.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Vref Landing Reference Speed\n\n**Pronunciation:** VEE-ref LAN-ding REF-er-ens speed\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Vref → VEE-ref\n- Landing → LAN-ding\n- Reference → REF-er-ens\n- Speed → speed\n\nPractice:\n\nVref... landing reference speed... one point three VS.\n\nTogether (exam answer style):\n\nVref is the landing reference speed, not less than one point three VS in the landing configuration.",
