    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Saying \"the stick is shaking\" instead of standard phraseology.  \n  ✔ Use: stick shaker, recovering, going around.\n\n- ❌ Claiming the topic is irrelevant because the H130 has no shaker.  \n  ✔ Learn the exam English, then map it to helicopter energy emergencies.\n\n- ❌ Pulling back against the shaker to hold the glidepath.  \n  ✔ Reduce angle of attack first. Glidepath is secondary to flying speed.\n\n- ❌ Omitting the reason on the go-around call.  \n  ✔ State stick shaker so ATC understands the urgency.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** ANAC123, Going Around, Stick Shaker, Recovering\n\n**Pronunciation:** AY-nak WUN TOO THREE, GO-ing uh-ROUND, STIK SHAY-ker, ree-KUH-vuh-ring\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Stick → STIK\n- Shaker → SHAY-ker (stress on first)\n- Recovering → ree-KUH-vuh-ring\n\nPractice:\n\nStick shaker... recovering... going around.\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, going around, stick shaker, recovering, request climb two thousand.",
