    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Continuing to land after a red deck call \"because we were committed.\"  \n  ✔ Go around. Red is mandatory wave-off.\n\n- ❌ Failing to report lifting to coastal control.  \n  ✔ Lifting calls maintain traffic and SAR picture.\n\n- ❌ Accepting amber without understanding the restriction.  \n  ✔ Clarify or go around. Ambiguity is not clearance.\n\n- ❌ Long company chat on the ATC frequency.  \n  ✔ Keep ATC concise; use company frequency for deck detail when available.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** ANAC123, Going Around, Helideck Red\n\n**Pronunciation:** AY-nak WUN TOO THREE, GO-ing uh-ROUND, HEL-ih-dek RED\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Helideck → HEL-ih-dek (stress on first)\n- Red → RED\n- Orbit → OR-bit\n\nPractice:\n\nHelideck red... going around... request orbit.\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, going around, helideck red, crane obstacle, request orbit east.",
