    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Long explanation of engine indications during the descent.  \n  ✔ Mayday, dual engine failure, autorotating, position.\n\n- ❌ Forgetting position in the offshore mayday.  \n  ✔ Position is what launches SAR to the right place.\n\n- ❌ Using pan-pan for total power loss.  \n  ✔ Dual engine failure is mayday.\n\n- ❌ Blocking the frequency after the initial call.  \n  ✔ Fly; answer briefly when ATC asks.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Mayday, Dual Engine Failure, Autorotating\n\n**Pronunciation:** AY-nak WUN TOO THREE, MAY-day, DOO-ul EN-jin FAYL-yer, AW-toh-roh-TAY-ting\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Dual → DOO-ul\n- Engine → EN-jin\n- Autorotating → AW-toh-roh-TAY-ting (stress on \"tay\")\n\nPractice:\n\nDual engine failure... autorotating.\n\nTogether:\n\nMayday mayday mayday, dual engine failure, autorotating, one zero miles east of Santos.",
