    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Requesting start while the fuel hose is still connected.  \n  ✔ Complete refuel and secure the aircraft first.\n\n- ❌ Not advising ATC of extended pad occupancy.  \n  ✔ Request time on pad for cold refuel.\n\n- ❌ Treating cold refuel as \"no radio needed.\"  \n  ✔ Keep ATC informed of status and readiness.\n\n- ❌ Shutting down in out-of-limit wind without care.  \n  ✔ Respect blade sail limits during shutdown.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Shutting Down for Cold Refuel\n\n**Pronunciation:** SHUT-ing DOWN for KOLD REE-fyool\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Shutting → SHUT-ing\n- Cold → KOLD\n- Refuel → REE-fyool\n\nPractice:\n\nShutting down for cold refuel... will advise ready for start.\n\nTogether:\n\nOn pad, shutting down for cold refuel, request time on pad, will advise ready.",
