    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Treating bypass as advisory and continuing the full mission.  \n  ✔ Land as soon as practicable — bypass is abnormal.\n\n- ❌ Declaring Mayday immediately with stable parameters and no power loss.  \n  ✔ Use Pan Pan when stable; Mayday when distress develops.\n\n- ❌ Omitting the system name and saying only \"fuel problem.\"  \n  ✔ Say fuel filter bypass so ATC and maintenance understand the threat.\n\n- ❌ Accepting holding while on bypass.  \n  ✔ Request priority and decline unnecessary delay.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Fuel Filter Bypass, Request Priority Landing\n\n**Pronunciation:** FYOOL FIL-ter BY-pass, reh-KWEST pry-OR-ih-tee LAN-ding\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Fuel → FYOOL\n- Filter → FIL-ter (stress on first)\n- Bypass → BY-pass (stress on first)\n- Priority → pry-OR-ih-tee\n\nPractice:\n\nFuel filter bypass... request priority landing.\n\nTogether:\n\nFuel filter bypass, reducing power, request priority landing.",
