    "displayTerm": "MGB Oil Pressure Low",
    "term": "mgb oil pressure low",
    "slug": "mgb-oil-pressure-low",
    "category": "Helicopter Operations",
    "meaningEn": "MGB Oil Pressure Low is an abnormal indication that main gearbox oil pressure has fallen below the minimum required for adequate lubrication of the main transmission.",
    "meaningPt": "Pressão de óleo baixa da caixa de transmissão principal (MGB).\n\nIndicação anormal de que a pressão do óleo da caixa principal caiu abaixo do mínimo necessário para lubrificação adequada da transmissão principal.",
    "whenUsed": "When MGB oil pressure is low, the pilot should:",
    "example": "Approach: ANAC123, roger Mayday, main gearbox oil pressure low, say souls on board.",
    "sayPhrase": "Mayday Mayday Mayday, Approach, ANAC123, MGB oil pressure low, reducing power, request immediate landing.",
    "icaoQuestion": "MGB oil pressure falls rapidly in cruise. What do you say to ATC?",
    "icaoSpeakText": "Mayday Mayday Mayday, Approach, main gearbox oil pressure low and falling, reducing power, request immediate landing nearest suitable. I would state position and souls on board as soon as practicable.",
    "missionBrief": "Today's lesson covers MGB Oil Pressure Low — a low main gearbox oil pressure indication that threatens lubrication of gears and bearings in the primary transmission.\n\nWithout adequate oil pressure, the main gearbox can overheat, seize, or fail catastrophically with little further warning.\n\nFor H130 helicopter operations, low MGB oil pressure is a critical emergency: reduce power, land as soon as possible, and communicate with Mayday when pressure is lost or falling with secondary symptoms.\n\nUnderstanding how to report MGB oil pressure low in ICAO-standard English is essential for Part 2 and Part 3 proficiency.",
    "captainTeaching": "Oil pressure is life for the main gearbox.\n\nWhen pressure falls, lubrication falls. Heat rises. Metal-to-metal contact can follow quickly.\n\nOn the H130, treat low MGB oil pressure as an immediate landing item. Reduce load. Do not climb. Do not accept delay.\n\nIf pressure collapses with vibration or rapid temperature rise, expect possible seizure. Keep an autorotation plan in mind while you fly to the nearest suitable site.\n\nSay the words clearly: main gearbox oil pressure low. Controllers must understand this is transmission critical — not a routine engine oil call.",
    "operationalContext": "You are at one thousand eight hundred feet in your H130 near Florianópolis.\n\nMGB oil pressure drops into the low caution range and continues falling. Temperature begins to rise. You reduce collective and select the nearest suitable landing site.\n\nYou declare Mayday, report main gearbox oil pressure low, and request immediate landing. Approach clears traffic. You land with minimum power, shut down, and request fire services until the area is secured.",
    "sayItCoach": "Main gearbox oil pressure low, reducing power, request immediate landing.",
    "icaoModelAnswer": "Mayday Mayday Mayday, Approach, main gearbox oil pressure low and falling, reducing power, request immediate landing nearest suitable. I would state position and souls on board as soon as practicable.",
    "memoryTrick": "**PRESS** — **P**ower down, **R**eport Mayday, **E**xit to nearest site, **S**can temp and vibration, **S**hut down after landing.",
    "operationalMeaning": "When MGB oil pressure is low, the pilot should:\n\nMGB oil pressure low reporting commonly includes:",
    "whyAtcUsesIt": [],
    "atcPhraseology": [
      "Approach: ANAC123, roger Mayday, main gearbox oil pressure low, say souls on board.",
      "Approach: ANAC123, nearest landing site twelve o'clock three miles, cleared as requested.",
      "Tower: ANAC123, cleared to land, emergency services standing by.",
      "Approach: ANAC123, say pressure trend and intentions.",
      "Tower: ANAC123, wind one eight zero at zero eight, report short final."
    ],
    "pilotReadbacks": [
      "Mayday Mayday Mayday, Approach, ANAC123, MGB oil pressure low, reducing power, request immediate landing.",
      "Mayday Mayday Mayday, ANAC123, main gearbox oil pressure failing, landing three miles ahead.",
      "ANAC123, Mayday, MGB low oil pressure, souls on board three, fuel remaining four zero minutes.",
      "ANAC123, proceeding to landing site, descending.",
      "Tower, ANAC123, short final, Mayday MGB oil pressure, request fire services."
    ],
    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Trying to reach home base with critically low MGB pressure.  \n  ✔ Land as soon as possible at the nearest suitable site.\n\n- ❌ Declaring only Pan Pan when pressure is collapsing.  \n  ✔ Use Mayday for significant MGB oil pressure loss.\n\n- ❌ Omitting \"main gearbox\" and saying only \"low oil pressure.\"  \n  ✔ Specify MGB so ATC understands transmission urgency.\n\n- ❌ Increasing collective to \"get there faster.\"  \n  ✔ Reduce load — high power accelerates gearbox damage.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Main Gearbox Oil Pressure Low, Request Immediate Landing\n\n**Pronunciation:** MAYN GEAR-boks OIL PRESH-ur LOH, reh-KWEST ih-MEE-dee-ut LAN-ding\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Gearbox → GEAR-boks\n- Pressure → PRESH-ur (stress on first)\n- Low → LOH\n- Immediate → ih-MEE-dee-ut\n\nPractice:\n\nMain gearbox oil pressure low... request immediate landing.\n\nTogether:\n\nMain gearbox oil pressure low, reducing power, request immediate landing.",
