    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Continuing the climb to cruise with T4 over red line.  \n  ✔ Reduce power immediately and land as required by the AFM.\n\n- ❌ Saying only \"engine problem\" without overtemp.  \n  ✔ State engine overtemp or turbine temperature exceedance.\n\n- ❌ Declining priority because the temperature \"came back.\"  \n  ✔ Still land for inspection after an exceedance.\n\n- ❌ Using high power on final after an overtemp event.  \n  ✔ Plan a minimum-power approach consistent with safety.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Engine Overtemp, Request Priority Landing\n\n**Pronunciation:** EN-jin OH-ver-temp, reh-KWEST pry-OR-ih-tee LAN-ding\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Engine → EN-jin (stress on first)\n- Overtemp → OH-ver-temp (stress on first)\n- Priority → pry-OR-ih-tee\n- Landing → LAN-ding\n\nPractice:\n\nEngine overtemp... request priority landing.\n\nTogether:\n\nEngine overtemp, reducing power, request priority landing.",
