    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Trusting the FMS without checking the clearance.  \n  ✔ Clearance and chart first; FMS must match both.\n\n- ❌ Changing altitude bugs without the other pilot verifying.  \n  ✔ Call the set; require a cross-check response.\n\n- ❌ Ignoring a small mismatch \"to save time.\"  \n  ✔ Resolve mismatches before the next phase of flight.\n\n- ❌ Feeling offended when challenged.  \n  ✔ Treat challenges as cross-checks, not criticism.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** ANAC123, Confirm Cleared ILS Runway One Four\n\n**Pronunciation:** AY-nak WUN TOO THREE, kun-FIRM KLEERD EYE-EL-ES RUN-way WUN FOR\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Confirm → kun-FIRM\n- Cleared → KLEERD\n- Runway → RUN-way\n- Four → FOR\n\nPractice:\n\nConfirm cleared ILS runway one four.\n\nTogether:\n\nANAC123, confirm cleared ILS runway one four, we had one six loaded.",
