    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Confusing hazard listing with actual risk assessment.  \n  ✔ Assess likelihood and severity, then decide mitigations.\n\n- ❌ Continuing because “we usually make it.”  \n  ✔ Use abort criteria set before the approach, not hope.\n\n- ❌ Failing to tell ATC when risk forces a plan change.  \n  ✔ Translate the decision into hold, orbit, or divert calls.\n\n- ❌ Assessing risk once at dispatch and never again.  \n  ✔ Reassess when weather, weight, or ATC plan changes.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Requesting Orbit to Assess Landing Conditions\n\n**Pronunciation:** reh-KWEST-ing OR-bit too uh-SESS LAN-ding kun-DISH-unz\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Requesting → reh-KWEST-ing\n- Orbit → OR-bit\n- Assess → uh-SESS\n- Conditions → kun-DISH-unz\n\nPractice:\n\nRequesting orbit... assess landing conditions... diverting.\n\nTogether:\n\nRequesting orbit to assess landing conditions, will advise intentions.",
