    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Seeing a hazard but not announcing it until too late.  \n  ✔ Call it early so the team can act.\n\n- ❌ Using vague words like “complicated” instead of the real hazard.  \n  ✔ Name the wire, wind, or performance limit specifically.\n\n- ❌ Treating hazard reports as optional paperwork.  \n  ✔ Recurring hazards need SMS visibility.\n\n- ❌ Focusing only on external hazards and ignoring fatigue or rushed briefs.  \n  ✔ Human-factor hazards count equally.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Going Around, Wires on Approach Path\n\n**Pronunciation:** GO-ing uh-ROUND, WY-erz on uh-PROHCH PATH\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Going → GO-ing\n- Around → uh-ROUND\n- Wires → WY-erz\n- Approach → uh-PROHCH\n\nPractice:\n\nGoing around... wires on approach path... unable to land.\n\nTogether:\n\nGoing around, wires on approach path, requesting reposition.",
