    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Describing Safety Culture only as company posters or manuals.  \n  ✔ Describe real behaviors under pressure and reporting habits.\n\n- ❌ Confusing Safety Culture with zero accidents by luck.  \n  ✔ Strong culture manages risk before the accident statistics move.\n\n- ❌ Punishing honest reporters while claiming a safety culture.  \n  ✔ Just Culture is a required pillar of Safety Culture.\n\n- ❌ Accepting “normal” shortcuts because seniors do them.  \n  ✔ Challenge normalized deviance — that is cultural leadership.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Unable to Land, Diverting, Safety Report\n\n**Pronunciation:** un-AY-bul too LAND, di-VUR-ting, SAYF-tee rih-PORT\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Unable → un-AY-bul\n- Diverting → di-VUR-ting\n- Safety → SAYF-tee\n- Report → rih-PORT\n\nPractice:\n\nUnable to land... diverting... voluntary safety report.\n\nTogether:\n\nUnable to land, diverting, will file a safety report after arrival.",
