    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Long Portuguese-style sentences with the main verb at the end.  \n  ✔ Put the action early: I would divert because...\n\n- ❌ Answering without a plan — jumping between ideas.  \n  ✔ Use PEEL or another fixed spine every time.\n\n- ❌ Overusing complex grammar that collapses under stress.  \n  ✔ Prefer simple clear sentences when workload rises.\n\n- ❌ Omitting subjects or verbs in plain language.  \n  ✔ Complete the clause: We are diverting to Congonhas.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Weather Below Minima, Diverting, Request Routing\n\n**Pronunciation:** WETH-er bih-LOH MIN-ih-muh, di-VUR-ting, reh-KWEST ROO-ting\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Weather → WETH-er\n- Below → bih-LOH\n- Minima → MIN-ih-muh\n- Diverting → di-VUR-ting\n\nPractice:\n\nWeather below minima... diverting... request routing.\n\nTogether:\n\nWeather below minima, diverting Congonhas, request routing.",
