    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Equating fluency with high speed.  \n  ✔ Use a steady professional rate that protects clarity.\n\n- ❌ Long silent gaps while searching for perfect grammar.  \n  ✔ Simplify and continue; repair later if needed.\n\n- ❌ Constant restarts of the same sentence.  \n  ✔ Finish a simple version; do not reboot endlessly.\n\n- ❌ Overusing fillers that distract the listener.  \n  ✔ Prefer a short silent pause or a connector word.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Going Around, Requesting Vectors for Second Approach\n\n**Pronunciation:** GO-ing uh-ROUND, reh-KWEST-ing VEK-torz for SEK-und uh-PROHCH\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Going → GO-ing\n- Requesting → reh-KWEST-ing\n- Vectors → VEK-torz\n- Approach → uh-PROHCH\n\nPractice as one continuous phrase:\n\nGoing around, requesting vectors for second approach.\n\nTogether at steady rate:\n\nGoing around, requesting vectors for second approach, will advise ready.",
