    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Guessing a missed altitude or heading to avoid saying say again.  \n  ✔ Request a repeat; never invent critical numbers.\n\n- ❌ Answering before the examiner finishes a two-part question.  \n  ✔ Listen to the end, then address each part.\n\n- ❌ Confusing “confirm” with automatic agreement.  \n  ✔ Confirm means check — answer affirmative or negative truthfully.\n\n- ❌ Ignoring accent or noise difficulty instead of clarifying.  \n  ✔ Clarification is a professional comprehension strategy.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** Say Again Altitude, Heading One Two Zero Copied\n\n**Pronunciation:** SAY uh-GEN AL-ti-tood, HED-ing WUN TOO ZE-ro KOP-eed\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Again → uh-GEN\n- Altitude → AL-ti-tood\n- Heading → HED-ing\n- Copied → KOP-eed\n\nPractice:\n\nSay again altitude... heading copied... confirm runway.\n\nTogether:\n\nSay again altitude, heading one two zero copied.",
