    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Mixing present and past with no control.  \n  ✔ Stay in past tenses for the story; use present only for the lesson now.\n\n- ❌ Starting in the middle with no setting.  \n  ✔ Open with when, where, and aircraft.\n\n- ❌ Endless detail with no ending.  \n  ✔ Close with result and one lesson learned.\n\n- ❌ Telling someone else's story with no personal action.  \n  ✔ Include what you did and decided.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** While I Was Cruising I Decided to Divert\n\n**Pronunciation:** wyl eye wuz KROO-zing eye dih-SY-did too dih-VERT\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Cruising → KROO-zing\n- Decided → dih-SY-did\n- Divert → dih-VERT\n- Safely → SAYF-lee\n\nPractice:\n\nWhile I was cruising... I decided to divert.\n\nTogether:\n\nWhile I was cruising, I decided to divert and we landed safely.",
