    "category": "ICAO Speaking",
    "meaningEn": "Future Plans Discussion is the ICAO speaking task type in which the candidate describes intended future actions related to aviation — training, operations, career, or flight planning — using appropriate future forms and supporting reasons, so that temporal language, coherence, and interactive skill can be assessed at Operational Level 4 or higher.",
    "meaningPt": "Discussão de planos futuros / Future Plans Discussion.\n\nTipo de tarefa oral da ICAO em que o candidato descreve ações futuras pretendidas relacionadas à aviação — treinamento, operações, carreira ou planejamento de voo — usando formas de futuro apropriadas e razões de apoio, para avaliar linguagem temporal, coerência e habilidade interativa no Nível Operacional 4 ou superior.",
    "whenUsed": "When discussing future plans, the candidate should:",
    "example": "Examiner: ANAC123, what are your plans for the next training season?",
    "sayPhrase": "ANAC123, planning recurrent training next month, continuing IFR line flying.",
    "icaoQuestion": "What are your professional plans for the next two years as a helicopter pilot?",
    "icaoSpeakText": "Over the next two years I plan to continue flying the H130 on IFR and EMS-type missions. I am going to complete recurrent training on schedule and improve my ICAO English to stay comfortably above Level 4. I also want to gain more experience in confined-area and hospital helipad operations because those missions require strong decision-making. If opportunities appear, I will consider an instructor path later, but my first priority is line proficiency and safe operations.",
    "missionBrief": "Today's lesson covers Future Plans Discussion — the ICAO oral exam task in which you talk about upcoming flying plans, career goals, or intended actions using future forms at Level 4 or above.\n\nFuture plans discussion is not vague wishing. It is clear intention language with reasons and conditions.\n\nIn Part 1, the examiner may ask about your next rating, a planned route, training goals, or what you will do after the test. You must use will / going to / plan to appropriately, give reasons, and handle follow-ups about timing and obstacles.\n\nFor H130 ICAO Delta candidates, this Medium-priority task still matters: it rounds out discourse range and often appears as a closing Part 1 exchange when the examiner shifts from technical topics to personal professional plans.\n\nUnderstanding how to discuss future plans in ICAO-standard English is essential for Part 1 proficiency.",
    "captainTeaching": "Future plans need intention plus reason.\n\n\"I will do training\" is thin. \"I am going to do recurrent training next month because my checkride window opens\" is Level 4.\n\nChoose forms with purpose: going to for planned decisions, will for decisions made in the moment or offers, plan to for formal intentions. Perfect accuracy is less important than clear meaning.\n\nWhen the examiner asks \"what if that fails?\", shift briefly into hypothetical language, then return to the main plan. Interaction and future discussion overlap.\n\nKeep it aviation-professional. Long personal stories waste time and dilute vocabulary demonstration.\n\nIn H130 careers, plans often include type ratings, EMS missions, offshore work, or instructor paths. Pick real goals and practice saying them with timeframe and reason.",
    "operationalContext": "Examiner: What are your plans after this language test?\n\nYou answer: I plan to complete my ICAO Level 4 documentation and continue H130 IFR line flying. Next month I am going to attend recurrent training. I want to improve my radiotelephony confidence in busy terminal airspace because that is where I still feel the most pressure. If I have time this year, I will also study for an additional rating.\n\nClear intention. Timeframe. Reason. Optional extra. The examiner asks one more why — you are ready.",
    "sayItCoach": "I plan to continue IFR line flying and complete recurrent training next month.",
    "icaoModelAnswer": "Over the next two years I plan to continue flying the H130 on IFR and EMS-type missions. I am going to complete recurrent training on schedule and improve my ICAO English to stay comfortably above Level 4. I also want to gain more experience in confined-area and hospital helipad operations because those missions require strong decision-making. If opportunities appear, I will consider an instructor path later, but my first priority is line proficiency and safe operations.",
    "memoryTrick": "**FUTURE** — **F**orm the intention clearly, **U**tter a timeframe, **T**ie a reason with because, **U**pdate with next steps, **R**espond to what-if briefly, **E**nd on a professional aviation goal.",
    "operationalMeaning": "When discussing future plans, the candidate should:\n\nA Level 4 future-plans answer typically includes:",
