    "brazilianMistakes": "- ❌ Using only present tense for future meaning without markers.  \n  ✔ Use will / going to / plan to with a timeframe.\n\n- ❌ Saying \"I don't know\" with no provisional plan.  \n  ✔ Offer a considered option and a reason.\n\n- ❌ Giving personal life details instead of professional plans.  \n  ✔ Keep the focus on training, flying, and ratings.\n\n- ❌ Stating a plan with no reason when asked why.  \n  ✔ Always support intentions with because + operational reason.",
    "pronunciationCoaching": "**Target Phrase:** I Plan to Continue IFR Line Flying\n\n**Pronunciation:** eye PLAN too kun-TIN-yoo EYE-eff-AR LYN FLY-ing\n\n**Word Stress**\n\n- Plan → PLAN\n- Continue → kun-TIN-yoo\n- Line → LYN\n- Flying → FLY-ing\n\nPractice:\n\nI plan to continue... IFR line flying.\n\nTogether:\n\nI plan to continue IFR line flying and complete recurrent training next month.",
